39#define SLAVE_ADDR1 0x70
40#define SLAVE_ADDR2 0x72

42static int panel_type;
43
44static const void *
45find_section(const void *_bdb, int section_id)
46{
47 const struct bdb_header *bdb = _bdb;
48 const u8 *base = _bdb;
49 int index = 0;
50 u32 total, current_size;
51 u8 current_id;
52
53 /* skip to first section */
54 index += bdb->header_size;
55 total = bdb->bdb_size;
56
57 /* walk the sections looking for section_id */
58 while (index + 3 < total) {
59 current_id = *(base + index);
60 index++;
61
62 current_size = *((const u16 *)(base + index));
63 index += 2;
64
65 /* The MIPI Sequence Block v3+ has a separate size field. */
66 if (current_id == BDB_MIPI_SEQUENCE && *(base + index) >= 3)
67 current_size = *((const u32 *)(base + index + 1));
68
69 if (index + current_size > total)
70 return NULL;
71
72 if (current_id == section_id)
73 return base + index;
74
75 index += current_size;
76 }
77
78 return NULL;
79}
80
81static u16
82get_blocksize(const void *p)
83{
84 const u16 *block_ptr;
85 u16 block_size;
86
87 block_ptr = (const u16 *)((const char *)p - 2);
88 block_size = *block_ptr;
89 return block_size;
90}

92static void
93fill_detail_timing_data(struct drm_display_mode *panel_fixed_mode,
94 const struct lvds_dvo_timing *dvo_timing)
95{
96 panel_fixed_mode->hdisplay = (dvo_timing->hactive_hi << 8) |
97 dvo_timing->hactive_lo;
98 panel_fixed_mode->hsync_start = panel_fixed_mode->hdisplay +
99 ((dvo_timing->hsync_off_hi << 8) | dvo_timing->hsync_off_lo);
100 panel_fixed_mode->hsync_end = panel_fixed_mode->hsync_start +
101 dvo_timing->hsync_pulse_width;
102 panel_fixed_mode->htotal = panel_fixed_mode->hdisplay +
103 ((dvo_timing->hblank_hi << 8) | dvo_timing->hblank_lo);
104
105 panel_fixed_mode->vdisplay = (dvo_timing->vactive_hi << 8) |
106 dvo_timing->vactive_lo;
107 panel_fixed_mode->vsync_start = panel_fixed_mode->vdisplay +
108 dvo_timing->vsync_off;
109 panel_fixed_mode->vsync_end = panel_fixed_mode->vsync_start +
110 dvo_timing->vsync_pulse_width;
111 panel_fixed_mode->vtotal = panel_fixed_mode->vdisplay +
112 ((dvo_timing->vblank_hi << 8) | dvo_timing->vblank_lo);
113 panel_fixed_mode->clock = dvo_timing->clock * 10;
114 panel_fixed_mode->type = DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;
115
116 if (dvo_timing->hsync_positive)
117 panel_fixed_mode->flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC;
118 else
119 panel_fixed_mode->flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
120
121 if (dvo_timing->vsync_positive)
122 panel_fixed_mode->flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC;
123 else
124 panel_fixed_mode->flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
125
126 /* Some VBTs have bogus h/vtotal values */
127 if (panel_fixed_mode->hsync_end > panel_fixed_mode->htotal)
128 panel_fixed_mode->htotal = panel_fixed_mode->hsync_end + 1;
129 if (panel_fixed_mode->vsync_end > panel_fixed_mode->vtotal)
130 panel_fixed_mode->vtotal = panel_fixed_mode->vsync_end + 1;
131
132 drm_mode_set_name(panel_fixed_mode);
133}
134
135static const struct lvds_dvo_timing *
136get_lvds_dvo_timing(const struct bdb_lvds_lfp_data *lvds_lfp_data,
137 const struct bdb_lvds_lfp_data_ptrs *lvds_lfp_data_ptrs,
138 int index)
139{
140 /*
141 * the size of fp_timing varies on the different platform.
142 * So calculate the DVO timing relative offset in LVDS data
143 * entry to get the DVO timing entry
144 */
145
146 int lfp_data_size =
147 lvds_lfp_data_ptrs->ptr[1].dvo_timing_offset -
148 lvds_lfp_data_ptrs->ptr[0].dvo_timing_offset;
149 int dvo_timing_offset =
150 lvds_lfp_data_ptrs->ptr[0].dvo_timing_offset -
151 lvds_lfp_data_ptrs->ptr[0].fp_timing_offset;
152#ifdef __NetBSD__
153 const char *entry = (const char *)lvds_lfp_data->data +
154 lfp_data_size * index;
155
156 return (const struct lvds_dvo_timing *)(entry + dvo_timing_offset);
157#else
158 char *entry = (char *)lvds_lfp_data->data + lfp_data_size * index;
159
160 return (struct lvds_dvo_timing *)(entry + dvo_timing_offset);
161#endif
162}
163
164/* get lvds_fp_timing entry
165 * this function may return NULL if the corresponding entry is invalid
166 */
167static const struct lvds_fp_timing *
168get_lvds_fp_timing(const struct bdb_header *bdb,
169 const struct bdb_lvds_lfp_data *data,
170 const struct bdb_lvds_lfp_data_ptrs *ptrs,
171 int index)
172{
173 size_t data_ofs = (const u8 *)data - (const u8 *)bdb;
174 u16 data_size = ((const u16 *)data)[-1]; /* stored in header */
175 size_t ofs;
176
177 if (index >= ARRAY_SIZE(ptrs->ptr))
178 return NULL;
179 ofs = ptrs->ptr[index].fp_timing_offset;
180 if (ofs < data_ofs ||
181 ofs + sizeof(struct lvds_fp_timing) > data_ofs + data_size)
182 return NULL;
183 return (const struct lvds_fp_timing *)((const u8 *)bdb + ofs);
184}

186/* Try to find integrated panel data */
187static void
188parse_lfp_panel_data(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
189 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
190{
191 const struct bdb_lvds_options *lvds_options;
192 const struct bdb_lvds_lfp_data *lvds_lfp_data;
193 const struct bdb_lvds_lfp_data_ptrs *lvds_lfp_data_ptrs;
194 const struct lvds_dvo_timing *panel_dvo_timing;
195 const struct lvds_fp_timing *fp_timing;
196 struct drm_display_mode *panel_fixed_mode;
197 int drrs_mode;
198
199 lvds_options = find_section(bdb, BDB_LVDS_OPTIONS);
200 if (!lvds_options)
201 return;
202
203 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_dither = lvds_options->pixel_dither;
204 if (lvds_options->panel_type == 0xff)
205 return;
206
207 panel_type = lvds_options->panel_type;
208
209 drrs_mode = (lvds_options->dps_panel_type_bits
210 >> (panel_type * 2)) & MODE_MASK;
211 /*
212 * VBT has static DRRS = 0 and seamless DRRS = 2.
213 * The below piece of code is required to adjust vbt.drrs_type
214 * to match the enum drrs_support_type.
215 */
216 switch (drrs_mode) {
217 case 0:
218 dev_priv->vbt.drrs_type = STATIC_DRRS_SUPPORT;
219 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DRRS supported mode is static\n");
220 break;
221 case 2:
222 dev_priv->vbt.drrs_type = SEAMLESS_DRRS_SUPPORT;
223 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DRRS supported mode is seamless\n");
224 break;
225 default:
226 dev_priv->vbt.drrs_type = DRRS_NOT_SUPPORTED;
227 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DRRS not supported (VBT input)\n");
228 break;
229 }
230
231 lvds_lfp_data = find_section(bdb, BDB_LVDS_LFP_DATA);
232 if (!lvds_lfp_data)
233 return;
234
235 lvds_lfp_data_ptrs = find_section(bdb, BDB_LVDS_LFP_DATA_PTRS);
236 if (!lvds_lfp_data_ptrs)
237 return;
238
239 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_vbt = 1;
240
241 panel_dvo_timing = get_lvds_dvo_timing(lvds_lfp_data,
242 lvds_lfp_data_ptrs,
243 lvds_options->panel_type);
244
245 panel_fixed_mode = kzalloc(sizeof(*panel_fixed_mode), GFP_KERNEL);
246 if (!panel_fixed_mode)
247 return;
248
249 fill_detail_timing_data(panel_fixed_mode, panel_dvo_timing);
250
251 dev_priv->vbt.lfp_lvds_vbt_mode = panel_fixed_mode;
252
253 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Found panel mode in BIOS VBT tables:\n");
254 drm_mode_debug_printmodeline(panel_fixed_mode);
255
256 fp_timing = get_lvds_fp_timing(bdb, lvds_lfp_data,
257 lvds_lfp_data_ptrs,
258 lvds_options->panel_type);
259 if (fp_timing) {
260 /* check the resolution, just to be sure */
261 if (fp_timing->x_res == panel_fixed_mode->hdisplay &&
262 fp_timing->y_res == panel_fixed_mode->vdisplay) {
263 dev_priv->vbt.bios_lvds_val = fp_timing->lvds_reg_val;
264 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT initial LVDS value %x\n",
265 dev_priv->vbt.bios_lvds_val);
266 }
267 }
268}
269
270static void
271parse_lfp_backlight(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
272 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
273{
274 const struct bdb_lfp_backlight_data *backlight_data;
275 const struct bdb_lfp_backlight_data_entry *entry;
276
277 backlight_data = find_section(bdb, BDB_LVDS_BACKLIGHT);
278 if (!backlight_data)
279 return;
280
281 if (backlight_data->entry_size != sizeof(backlight_data->data[0])) {
282 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unsupported backlight data entry size %u\n",
283 backlight_data->entry_size);
284 return;
285 }
286
287 entry = &backlight_data->data[panel_type];
288
289 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.present = entry->type == BDB_BACKLIGHT_TYPE_PWM;
290 if (!dev_priv->vbt.backlight.present) {
291 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("PWM backlight not present in VBT (type %u)\n",
292 entry->type);
293 return;
294 }
295
296 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.pwm_freq_hz = entry->pwm_freq_hz;
297 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.active_low_pwm = entry->active_low_pwm;
298 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.min_brightness = entry->min_brightness;
299 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT backlight PWM modulation frequency %u Hz, "
300 "active %s, min brightness %u, level %u\n",
301 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.pwm_freq_hz,
302 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.active_low_pwm ? "low" : "high",
303 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.min_brightness,
304 backlight_data->level[panel_type]);
305}

307/* Try to find sdvo panel data */
308static void
309parse_sdvo_panel_data(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
310 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
311{
312 const struct lvds_dvo_timing *dvo_timing;
313 struct drm_display_mode *panel_fixed_mode;
314 int index;
315
316 index = i915.vbt_sdvo_panel_type;
317 if (index == -2) {
318 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Ignore SDVO panel mode from BIOS VBT tables.\n");
319 return;
320 }
321
322 if (index == -1) {
323 const struct bdb_sdvo_lvds_options *sdvo_lvds_options;
324
325 sdvo_lvds_options = find_section(bdb, BDB_SDVO_LVDS_OPTIONS);
326 if (!sdvo_lvds_options)
327 return;
328
329 index = sdvo_lvds_options->panel_type;
330 }
331
332 dvo_timing = find_section(bdb, BDB_SDVO_PANEL_DTDS);
333 if (!dvo_timing)
334 return;
335
336 panel_fixed_mode = kzalloc(sizeof(*panel_fixed_mode), GFP_KERNEL);
337 if (!panel_fixed_mode)
338 return;
339
340 fill_detail_timing_data(panel_fixed_mode, dvo_timing + index);
341
342 dev_priv->vbt.sdvo_lvds_vbt_mode = panel_fixed_mode;
343
344 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Found SDVO panel mode in BIOS VBT tables:\n");
345 drm_mode_debug_printmodeline(panel_fixed_mode);
346}

348static int intel_bios_ssc_frequency(struct drm_device *dev,
349 bool alternate)
350{
351 switch (INTEL_INFO(dev)->gen) {
352 case 2:
353 return alternate ? 66667 : 48000;
354 case 3:
355 case 4:
356 return alternate ? 100000 : 96000;
357 default:
358 return alternate ? 100000 : 120000;
359 }
360}

362static void
363parse_general_features(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
364 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
365{
366 struct drm_device *dev = dev_priv->dev;
367 const struct bdb_general_features *general;
368
369 general = find_section(bdb, BDB_GENERAL_FEATURES);
370 if (general) {
371 dev_priv->vbt.int_tv_support = general->int_tv_support;
372 dev_priv->vbt.int_crt_support = general->int_crt_support;
373 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_use_ssc = general->enable_ssc;
374 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_ssc_freq =
375 intel_bios_ssc_frequency(dev, general->ssc_freq);
376 dev_priv->vbt.display_clock_mode = general->display_clock_mode;
377 dev_priv->vbt.fdi_rx_polarity_inverted = general->fdi_rx_polarity_inverted;
378 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("BDB_GENERAL_FEATURES int_tv_support %d int_crt_support %d lvds_use_ssc %d lvds_ssc_freq %d display_clock_mode %d fdi_rx_polarity_inverted %d\n",
379 dev_priv->vbt.int_tv_support,
380 dev_priv->vbt.int_crt_support,
381 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_use_ssc,
382 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_ssc_freq,
383 dev_priv->vbt.display_clock_mode,
384 dev_priv->vbt.fdi_rx_polarity_inverted);
385 }
386}
387
388static void
389parse_general_definitions(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
390 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
391{
392 const struct bdb_general_definitions *general;
393
394 general = find_section(bdb, BDB_GENERAL_DEFINITIONS);
395 if (general) {
396 u16 block_size = get_blocksize(general);
397 if (block_size >= sizeof(*general)) {
398 int bus_pin = general->crt_ddc_gmbus_pin;
399 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("crt_ddc_bus_pin: %d\n", bus_pin);
400 if (intel_gmbus_is_valid_pin(dev_priv, bus_pin))
401 dev_priv->vbt.crt_ddc_pin = bus_pin;
402 } else {
403 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("BDB_GD too small (%d). Invalid.\n",
404 block_size);
405 }
406 }
407}
408
409static const union child_device_config *
410child_device_ptr(const struct bdb_general_definitions *p_defs, int i)
411{
412 return (const void *) &p_defs->devices[i * p_defs->child_dev_size];
413}
414
415static void
416parse_sdvo_device_mapping(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
417 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
418{
419 struct sdvo_device_mapping *p_mapping;
420 const struct bdb_general_definitions *p_defs;
421 const struct old_child_dev_config *child; /* legacy */
422 int i, child_device_num, count;
423 u16 block_size;
424
425 p_defs = find_section(bdb, BDB_GENERAL_DEFINITIONS);
426 if (!p_defs) {
427 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No general definition block is found, unable to construct sdvo mapping.\n");
428 return;
429 }
430
431 /*
432 * Only parse SDVO mappings when the general definitions block child
433 * device size matches that of the *legacy* child device config
434 * struct. Thus, SDVO mapping will be skipped for newer VBT.
435 */
436 if (p_defs->child_dev_size != sizeof(*child)) {
437 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unsupported child device size for SDVO mapping.\n");
438 return;
439 }
440 /* get the block size of general definitions */
441 block_size = get_blocksize(p_defs);
442 /* get the number of child device */
443 child_device_num = (block_size - sizeof(*p_defs)) /
444 p_defs->child_dev_size;
445 count = 0;
446 for (i = 0; i < child_device_num; i++) {
447 child = &child_device_ptr(p_defs, i)->old;
448 if (!child->device_type) {
449 /* skip the device block if device type is invalid */
450 continue;
451 }
452 if (child->slave_addr != SLAVE_ADDR1 &&
453 child->slave_addr != SLAVE_ADDR2) {
454 /*
455 * If the slave address is neither 0x70 nor 0x72,
456 * it is not a SDVO device. Skip it.
457 */
458 continue;
459 }
460 if (child->dvo_port != DEVICE_PORT_DVOB &&
461 child->dvo_port != DEVICE_PORT_DVOC) {
462 /* skip the incorrect SDVO port */
463 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Incorrect SDVO port. Skip it\n");
464 continue;
465 }
466 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("the SDVO device with slave addr %2x is found on"
467 " %s port\n",
468 child->slave_addr,
469 (child->dvo_port == DEVICE_PORT_DVOB) ?
470 "SDVOB" : "SDVOC");
471 p_mapping = &(dev_priv->sdvo_mappings[child->dvo_port - 1]);
472 if (!p_mapping->initialized) {
473 p_mapping->dvo_port = child->dvo_port;
474 p_mapping->slave_addr = child->slave_addr;
475 p_mapping->dvo_wiring = child->dvo_wiring;
476 p_mapping->ddc_pin = child->ddc_pin;
477 p_mapping->i2c_pin = child->i2c_pin;
478 p_mapping->initialized = 1;
479 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SDVO device: dvo=%x, addr=%x, wiring=%d, ddc_pin=%d, i2c_pin=%d\n",
480 p_mapping->dvo_port,
481 p_mapping->slave_addr,
482 p_mapping->dvo_wiring,
483 p_mapping->ddc_pin,
484 p_mapping->i2c_pin);
485 } else {
486 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Maybe one SDVO port is shared by "
487 "two SDVO device.\n");
488 }
489 if (child->slave2_addr) {
490 /* Maybe this is a SDVO device with multiple inputs */
491 /* And the mapping info is not added */
492 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("there exists the slave2_addr. Maybe this"
493 " is a SDVO device with multiple inputs.\n");
494 }
495 count++;
496 }
497
498 if (!count) {
499 /* No SDVO device info is found */
500 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No SDVO device info is found in VBT\n");
501 }
502 return;
503}
504
505static void
506parse_driver_features(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
507 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
508{
509 const struct bdb_driver_features *driver;
510
511 driver = find_section(bdb, BDB_DRIVER_FEATURES);
512 if (!driver)
513 return;
514
515 if (driver->lvds_config == BDB_DRIVER_FEATURE_EDP)
516 dev_priv->vbt.edp_support = 1;
517
518 if (driver->dual_frequency)
519 dev_priv->render_reclock_avail = true;
520
521 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("DRRS State Enabled:%d\n", driver->drrs_enabled);
522 /*
523 * If DRRS is not supported, drrs_type has to be set to 0.
524 * This is because, VBT is configured in such a way that
525 * static DRRS is 0 and DRRS not supported is represented by
526 * driver->drrs_enabled=false
527 */
528 if (!driver->drrs_enabled)
529 dev_priv->vbt.drrs_type = DRRS_NOT_SUPPORTED;
530}
531
532static void
533parse_edp(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, const struct bdb_header *bdb)
534{
535 const struct bdb_edp *edp;
536 const struct edp_power_seq *edp_pps;
537 const struct edp_link_params *edp_link_params;
538
539 edp = find_section(bdb, BDB_EDP);
540 if (!edp) {
541 if (dev_priv->vbt.edp_support)
542 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No eDP BDB found but eDP panel supported.\n");
543 return;
544 }
545
546 switch ((edp->color_depth >> (panel_type * 2)) & 3) {
547 case EDP_18BPP:
548 dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp = 18;
549 break;
550 case EDP_24BPP:
551 dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp = 24;
552 break;
553 case EDP_30BPP:
554 dev_priv->vbt.edp_bpp = 30;
555 break;
556 }
557
558 /* Get the eDP sequencing and link info */
559 edp_pps = &edp->power_seqs[panel_type];
560 edp_link_params = &edp->link_params[panel_type];
561
562 dev_priv->vbt.edp_pps = *edp_pps;
563
564 switch (edp_link_params->rate) {
565 case EDP_RATE_1_62:
566 dev_priv->vbt.edp_rate = DP_LINK_BW_1_62;
567 break;
568 case EDP_RATE_2_7:
569 dev_priv->vbt.edp_rate = DP_LINK_BW_2_7;
570 break;
571 default:
572 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT has unknown eDP link rate value %u\n",
573 edp_link_params->rate);
574 break;
575 }
576
577 switch (edp_link_params->lanes) {
578 case EDP_LANE_1:
579 dev_priv->vbt.edp_lanes = 1;
580 break;
581 case EDP_LANE_2:
582 dev_priv->vbt.edp_lanes = 2;
583 break;
584 case EDP_LANE_4:
585 dev_priv->vbt.edp_lanes = 4;
586 break;
587 default:
588 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT has unknown eDP lane count value %u\n",
589 edp_link_params->lanes);
590 break;
591 }
592
593 switch (edp_link_params->preemphasis) {
594 case EDP_PREEMPHASIS_NONE:
595 dev_priv->vbt.edp_preemphasis = DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_0;
596 break;
597 case EDP_PREEMPHASIS_3_5dB:
598 dev_priv->vbt.edp_preemphasis = DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_1;
599 break;
600 case EDP_PREEMPHASIS_6dB:
601 dev_priv->vbt.edp_preemphasis = DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_2;
602 break;
603 case EDP_PREEMPHASIS_9_5dB:
604 dev_priv->vbt.edp_preemphasis = DP_TRAIN_PRE_EMPH_LEVEL_3;
605 break;
606 default:
607 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT has unknown eDP pre-emphasis value %u\n",
608 edp_link_params->preemphasis);
609 break;
610 }
611
612 switch (edp_link_params->vswing) {
613 case EDP_VSWING_0_4V:
614 dev_priv->vbt.edp_vswing = DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_0;
615 break;
616 case EDP_VSWING_0_6V:
617 dev_priv->vbt.edp_vswing = DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_1;
618 break;
619 case EDP_VSWING_0_8V:
620 dev_priv->vbt.edp_vswing = DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_2;
621 break;
622 case EDP_VSWING_1_2V:
623 dev_priv->vbt.edp_vswing = DP_TRAIN_VOLTAGE_SWING_LEVEL_3;
624 break;
625 default:
626 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT has unknown eDP voltage swing value %u\n",
627 edp_link_params->vswing);
628 break;
629 }
630
631 if (bdb->version >= 173) {
632 uint8_t vswing;
633
634 /* Don't read from VBT if module parameter has valid value*/
635 if (i915.edp_vswing) {
636 dev_priv->edp_low_vswing = i915.edp_vswing == 1;
637 } else {
638 vswing = (edp->edp_vswing_preemph >> (panel_type * 4)) & 0xF;
639 dev_priv->edp_low_vswing = vswing == 0;
640 }
641 }
642}
643
644static void
645parse_psr(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, const struct bdb_header *bdb)
646{
647 const struct bdb_psr *psr;
648 const struct psr_table *psr_table;
649
650 psr = find_section(bdb, BDB_PSR);
651 if (!psr) {
652 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No PSR BDB found.\n");
653 return;
654 }
655
656 psr_table = &psr->psr_table[panel_type];
657
658 dev_priv->vbt.psr.full_link = psr_table->full_link;
659 dev_priv->vbt.psr.require_aux_wakeup = psr_table->require_aux_to_wakeup;
660
661 /* Allowed VBT values goes from 0 to 15 */
662 dev_priv->vbt.psr.idle_frames = psr_table->idle_frames < 0 ? 0 :
663 psr_table->idle_frames > 15 ? 15 : psr_table->idle_frames;
664
665 switch (psr_table->lines_to_wait) {
666 case 0:
667 dev_priv->vbt.psr.lines_to_wait = PSR_0_LINES_TO_WAIT;
668 break;
669 case 1:
670 dev_priv->vbt.psr.lines_to_wait = PSR_1_LINE_TO_WAIT;
671 break;
672 case 2:
673 dev_priv->vbt.psr.lines_to_wait = PSR_4_LINES_TO_WAIT;
674 break;
675 case 3:
676 dev_priv->vbt.psr.lines_to_wait = PSR_8_LINES_TO_WAIT;
677 break;
678 default:
679 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT has unknown PSR lines to wait %u\n",
680 psr_table->lines_to_wait);
681 break;
682 }
683
684 dev_priv->vbt.psr.tp1_wakeup_time = psr_table->tp1_wakeup_time;
685 dev_priv->vbt.psr.tp2_tp3_wakeup_time = psr_table->tp2_tp3_wakeup_time;
686}
687
688static u8 *goto_next_sequence(u8 *data, int *size)
689{
690 u16 len;
691 int tmp = *size;
692
693 if (--tmp < 0)
694 return NULL;
695
696 /* goto first element */
697 data++;
698 while (1) {
699 switch (*data) {
700 case MIPI_SEQ_ELEM_SEND_PKT:
701 /*
702 * skip by this element payload size
703 * skip elem id, command flag and data type
704 */
705 tmp -= 5;
706 if (tmp < 0)
707 return NULL;
708
709 data += 3;
710 len = *((u16 *)data);
711
712 tmp -= len;
713 if (tmp < 0)
714 return NULL;
715
716 /* skip by len */
717 data = data + 2 + len;
718 break;
719 case MIPI_SEQ_ELEM_DELAY:
720 /* skip by elem id, and delay is 4 bytes */
721 tmp -= 5;
722 if (tmp < 0)
723 return NULL;
724
725 data += 5;
726 break;
727 case MIPI_SEQ_ELEM_GPIO:
728 tmp -= 3;
729 if (tmp < 0)
730 return NULL;
731
732 data += 3;
733 break;
734 default:
735 DRM_ERROR("Unknown element\n");
736 return NULL;
737 }
738
739 /* end of sequence ? */
740 if (*data == 0)
741 break;
742 }
743
744 /* goto next sequence or end of block byte */
745 if (--tmp < 0)
746 return NULL;
747
748 data++;
749
750 /* update amount of data left for the sequence block to be parsed */
751 *size = tmp;
752 return data;
753}
754
755static void
756parse_mipi(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, const struct bdb_header *bdb)
757{
758 const struct bdb_mipi_config *start;
759 const struct bdb_mipi_sequence *sequence;
760 const struct mipi_config *config;
761 const struct mipi_pps_data *pps;
762 u8 *data;
763 const u8 *seq_data;
764 int i, panel_id, seq_size;
765 u16 block_size;
766
767 /* parse MIPI blocks only if LFP type is MIPI */
768 if (!dev_priv->vbt.has_mipi)
769 return;
770
771 /* Initialize this to undefined indicating no generic MIPI support */
772 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.panel_id = MIPI_DSI_UNDEFINED_PANEL_ID;
773
774 /* Block #40 is already parsed and panel_fixed_mode is
775 * stored in dev_priv->lfp_lvds_vbt_mode
776 * resuse this when needed
777 */
778
779 /* Parse #52 for panel index used from panel_type already
780 * parsed
781 */
782 start = find_section(bdb, BDB_MIPI_CONFIG);
783 if (!start) {
784 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No MIPI config BDB found");
785 return;
786 }
787
788 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("Found MIPI Config block, panel index = %d\n",
789 panel_type);
790
791 /*
792 * get hold of the correct configuration block and pps data as per
793 * the panel_type as index
794 */
795 config = &start->config[panel_type];
796 pps = &start->pps[panel_type];
797
798 /* store as of now full data. Trim when we realise all is not needed */
799 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.config = kmemdup(config, sizeof(struct mipi_config), GFP_KERNEL);
800 if (!dev_priv->vbt.dsi.config)
801 return;
802
803 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.pps = kmemdup(pps, sizeof(struct mipi_pps_data), GFP_KERNEL);
804 if (!dev_priv->vbt.dsi.pps) {
805 kfree(dev_priv->vbt.dsi.config);
806 return;
807 }
808
809 /* We have mandatory mipi config blocks. Initialize as generic panel */
810 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.panel_id = MIPI_DSI_GENERIC_PANEL_ID;
811
812 /* Check if we have sequence block as well */
813 sequence = find_section(bdb, BDB_MIPI_SEQUENCE);
814 if (!sequence) {
815 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No MIPI Sequence found, parsing complete\n");
816 return;
817 }
818
819 /* Fail gracefully for forward incompatible sequence block. */
820 if (sequence->version >= 3) {
821 DRM_ERROR("Unable to parse MIPI Sequence Block v3+\n");
822 return;
823 }
824
825 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("Found MIPI sequence block\n");
826
827 block_size = get_blocksize(sequence);
828
829 /*
830 * parse the sequence block for individual sequences
831 */
832 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.seq_version = sequence->version;
833
834 seq_data = &sequence->data[0];
835
836 /*
837 * sequence block is variable length and hence we need to parse and
838 * get the sequence data for specific panel id
839 */
840 for (i = 0; i < MAX_MIPI_CONFIGURATIONS; i++) {
841 panel_id = *seq_data;
842 seq_size = *((const u16 *) (seq_data + 1));
843 if (panel_id == panel_type)
844 break;
845
846 /* skip the sequence including seq header of 3 bytes */
847 seq_data = seq_data + 3 + seq_size;
848 if ((seq_data - &sequence->data[0]) > block_size) {
849 DRM_ERROR("Sequence start is beyond sequence block size, corrupted sequence block\n");
850 return;
851 }
852 }
853
854 if (i == MAX_MIPI_CONFIGURATIONS) {
855 DRM_ERROR("Sequence block detected but no valid configuration\n");
856 return;
857 }
858
859 /* check if found sequence is completely within the sequence block
860 * just being paranoid */
861 if (seq_size > block_size) {
862 DRM_ERROR("Corrupted sequence/size, bailing out\n");
863 return;
864 }
865
866 /* skip the panel id(1 byte) and seq size(2 bytes) */
867 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.data = kmemdup(seq_data + 3, seq_size, GFP_KERNEL);
868 if (!dev_priv->vbt.dsi.data)
869 return;
870
871 /*
872 * loop into the sequence data and split into multiple sequneces
873 * There are only 5 types of sequences as of now
874 */
875 data = dev_priv->vbt.dsi.data;
876 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.size = seq_size;
877
878 /* two consecutive 0x00 indicate end of all sequences */
879 while (1) {
880 int seq_id = *data;
881 if (MIPI_SEQ_MAX > seq_id && seq_id > MIPI_SEQ_UNDEFINED) {
882 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.sequence[seq_id] = data;
883 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("Found mipi sequence - %d\n", seq_id);
884 } else {
885 DRM_ERROR("undefined sequence\n");
886 goto err;
887 }
888
889 /* partial parsing to skip elements */
890 data = goto_next_sequence(data, &seq_size);
891
892 if (data == NULL) {
893 DRM_ERROR("Sequence elements going beyond block itself. Sequence block parsing failed\n");
894 goto err;
895 }
896
897 if (*data == 0)
898 break; /* end of sequence reached */
899 }
900
901 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("MIPI related vbt parsing complete\n");
902 return;
903err:
904 kfree(dev_priv->vbt.dsi.data);
905 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.data = NULL;
906
907 /* error during parsing so set all pointers to null
908 * because of partial parsing */
909 memset(dev_priv->vbt.dsi.sequence, 0, sizeof(dev_priv->vbt.dsi.sequence));
910}
911
912static u8 translate_iboost(u8 val)
913{
914 static const u8 mapping[] = { 1, 3, 7 }; /* See VBT spec */
915
916 if (val >= ARRAY_SIZE(mapping)) {
917 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unsupported I_boost value found in VBT (%d), display may not work properly\n", val);
918 return 0;
919 }
920 return mapping[val];
921}
922
923static void parse_ddi_port(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, enum port port,
924 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
925{
926 union child_device_config *it, *child = NULL;
927 struct ddi_vbt_port_info *info = &dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[port];
928 uint8_t hdmi_level_shift;
929 int i, j;
930 bool is_dvi, is_hdmi, is_dp, is_edp, is_crt;
931 uint8_t aux_channel, ddc_pin;
932 /* Each DDI port can have more than one value on the "DVO Port" field,
933 * so look for all the possible values for each port and abort if more
934 * than one is found. */
935 int dvo_ports[][3] = {
936 {DVO_PORT_HDMIA, DVO_PORT_DPA, -1},
937 {DVO_PORT_HDMIB, DVO_PORT_DPB, -1},
938 {DVO_PORT_HDMIC, DVO_PORT_DPC, -1},
939 {DVO_PORT_HDMID, DVO_PORT_DPD, -1},
940 {DVO_PORT_CRT, DVO_PORT_HDMIE, DVO_PORT_DPE},
941 };
942
943 /* Find the child device to use, abort if more than one found. */
944 for (i = 0; i < dev_priv->vbt.child_dev_num; i++) {
945 it = dev_priv->vbt.child_dev + i;
946
947 for (j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
948 if (dvo_ports[port][j] == -1)
949 break;
950
951 if (it->common.dvo_port == dvo_ports[port][j]) {
952 if (child) {
953 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("More than one child device for port %c in VBT.\n",
954 port_name(port));
955 return;
956 }
957 child = it;
958 }
959 }
960 }
961 if (!child)
962 return;
963
964 aux_channel = child->raw[25];
965 ddc_pin = child->common.ddc_pin;
966
967 is_dvi = child->common.device_type & DEVICE_TYPE_TMDS_DVI_SIGNALING;
968 is_dp = child->common.device_type & DEVICE_TYPE_DISPLAYPORT_OUTPUT;
969 is_crt = child->common.device_type & DEVICE_TYPE_ANALOG_OUTPUT;
970 is_hdmi = is_dvi && (child->common.device_type & DEVICE_TYPE_NOT_HDMI_OUTPUT) == 0;
971 is_edp = is_dp && (child->common.device_type & DEVICE_TYPE_INTERNAL_CONNECTOR);
972
973 if (port == PORT_A && is_dvi) {
974 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT claims port A supports DVI%s, ignoring\n",
975 is_hdmi ? "/HDMI" : "");
976 is_dvi = false;
977 is_hdmi = false;
978 }
979
980 info->supports_dvi = is_dvi;
981 info->supports_hdmi = is_hdmi;
982 info->supports_dp = is_dp;
983
984 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Port %c VBT info: DP:%d HDMI:%d DVI:%d EDP:%d CRT:%d\n",
985 port_name(port), is_dp, is_hdmi, is_dvi, is_edp, is_crt);
986
987 if (is_edp && is_dvi)
988 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Internal DP port %c is TMDS compatible\n",
989 port_name(port));
990 if (is_crt && port != PORT_E)
991 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Port %c is analog\n", port_name(port));
992 if (is_crt && (is_dvi || is_dp))
993 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Analog port %c is also DP or TMDS compatible\n",
994 port_name(port));
995 if (is_dvi && (port == PORT_A || port == PORT_E))
996 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Port %c is TMDS compatible\n", port_name(port));
997 if (!is_dvi && !is_dp && !is_crt)
998 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Port %c is not DP/TMDS/CRT compatible\n",
999 port_name(port));
1000 if (is_edp && (port == PORT_B || port == PORT_C || port == PORT_E))
1001 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Port %c is internal DP\n", port_name(port));
1002
1003 if (is_dvi) {
1004 if (port == PORT_E) {
1005 info->alternate_ddc_pin = ddc_pin;
1006 /* if DDIE share ddc pin with other port, then
1007 * dvi/hdmi couldn't exist on the shared port.
1008 * Otherwise they share the same ddc bin and system
1009 * couldn't communicate with them seperately. */
1010 if (ddc_pin == DDC_PIN_B) {
1011 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_B].supports_dvi = 0;
1012 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_B].supports_hdmi = 0;
1013 } else if (ddc_pin == DDC_PIN_C) {
1014 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_C].supports_dvi = 0;
1015 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_C].supports_hdmi = 0;
1016 } else if (ddc_pin == DDC_PIN_D) {
1017 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_D].supports_dvi = 0;
1018 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_D].supports_hdmi = 0;
1019 }
1020 } else if (ddc_pin == DDC_PIN_B && port != PORT_B)
1021 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unexpected DDC pin for port B\n");
1022 else if (ddc_pin == DDC_PIN_C && port != PORT_C)
1023 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unexpected DDC pin for port C\n");
1024 else if (ddc_pin == DDC_PIN_D && port != PORT_D)
1025 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unexpected DDC pin for port D\n");
1026 }
1027
1028 if (is_dp) {
1029 if (port == PORT_E) {
1030 info->alternate_aux_channel = aux_channel;
1031 /* if DDIE share aux channel with other port, then
1032 * DP couldn't exist on the shared port. Otherwise
1033 * they share the same aux channel and system
1034 * couldn't communicate with them seperately. */
1035 if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_A)
1036 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_A].supports_dp = 0;
1037 else if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_B)
1038 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_B].supports_dp = 0;
1039 else if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_C)
1040 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_C].supports_dp = 0;
1041 else if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_D)
1042 dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[PORT_D].supports_dp = 0;
1043 }
1044 else if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_A && port != PORT_A)
1045 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unexpected AUX channel for port A\n");
1046 else if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_B && port != PORT_B)
1047 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unexpected AUX channel for port B\n");
1048 else if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_C && port != PORT_C)
1049 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unexpected AUX channel for port C\n");
1050 else if (aux_channel == DP_AUX_D && port != PORT_D)
1051 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Unexpected AUX channel for port D\n");
1052 }
1053
1054 if (bdb->version >= 158) {
1055 /* The VBT HDMI level shift values match the table we have. */
1056 hdmi_level_shift = child->raw[7] & 0xF;
1057 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT HDMI level shift for port %c: %d\n",
1058 port_name(port),
1059 hdmi_level_shift);
1060 info->hdmi_level_shift = hdmi_level_shift;
1061 }
1062
1063 /* Parse the I_boost config for SKL and above */
1064 if (bdb->version >= 196 && (child->common.flags_1 & IBOOST_ENABLE)) {
1065 info->dp_boost_level = translate_iboost(child->common.iboost_level & 0xF);
1066 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT (e)DP boost level for port %c: %d\n",
1067 port_name(port), info->dp_boost_level);
1068 info->hdmi_boost_level = translate_iboost(child->common.iboost_level >> 4);
1069 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("VBT HDMI boost level for port %c: %d\n",
1070 port_name(port), info->hdmi_boost_level);
1071 }
1072}
1073
1074static void parse_ddi_ports(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
1075 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
1076{
1077 struct drm_device *dev = dev_priv->dev;
1078 enum port port;
1079
1080 if (!HAS_DDI(dev))
1081 return;
1082
1083 if (!dev_priv->vbt.child_dev_num)
1084 return;
1085
1086 if (bdb->version < 155)
1087 return;
1088
1089 for (port = PORT_A; port < I915_MAX_PORTS; port++)
1090 parse_ddi_port(dev_priv, port, bdb);
1091}
1092
1093static void
1094parse_device_mapping(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv,
1095 const struct bdb_header *bdb)
1096{
1097 const struct bdb_general_definitions *p_defs;
1098 const union child_device_config *p_child;
1099 union child_device_config *child_dev_ptr;
1100 int i, child_device_num, count;
1101 u8 expected_size;
1102 u16 block_size;
1103
1104 p_defs = find_section(bdb, BDB_GENERAL_DEFINITIONS);
1105 if (!p_defs) {
1106 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No general definition block is found, no devices defined.\n");
1107 return;
1108 }
1109 if (bdb->version < 195) {
1110 expected_size = sizeof(struct old_child_dev_config);
1111 } else if (bdb->version == 195) {
1112 expected_size = 37;
1113 } else if (bdb->version <= 197) {
1114 expected_size = 38;
1115 } else {
1116 expected_size = 38;
1117 BUILD_BUG_ON(sizeof(*p_child) < 38);
1118 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("Expected child device config size for VBT version %u not known; assuming %u\n",
1119 bdb->version, expected_size);
1120 }
1121
1122 /* The legacy sized child device config is the minimum we need. */
1123 if (p_defs->child_dev_size < sizeof(struct old_child_dev_config)) {
1124 DRM_ERROR("Child device config size %u is too small.\n",
1125 p_defs->child_dev_size);
1126 return;
1127 }
1128
1129 /* Flag an error for unexpected size, but continue anyway. */
1130 if (p_defs->child_dev_size != expected_size)
1131 DRM_ERROR("Unexpected child device config size %u (expected %u for VBT version %u)\n",
1132 p_defs->child_dev_size, expected_size, bdb->version);
1133
1134 /* get the block size of general definitions */
1135 block_size = get_blocksize(p_defs);
1136 /* get the number of child device */
1137 child_device_num = (block_size - sizeof(*p_defs)) /
1138 p_defs->child_dev_size;
1139 count = 0;
1140 /* get the number of child device that is present */
1141 for (i = 0; i < child_device_num; i++) {
1142 p_child = child_device_ptr(p_defs, i);
1143 if (!p_child->common.device_type) {
1144 /* skip the device block if device type is invalid */
1145 continue;
1146 }
1147 count++;
1148 }
1149 if (!count) {
1150 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("no child dev is parsed from VBT\n");
1151 return;
1152 }
1153 dev_priv->vbt.child_dev = kcalloc(count, sizeof(*p_child), GFP_KERNEL);
1154 if (!dev_priv->vbt.child_dev) {
1155 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("No memory space for child device\n");
1156 return;
1157 }
1158
1159 dev_priv->vbt.child_dev_num = count;
1160 count = 0;
1161 for (i = 0; i < child_device_num; i++) {
1162 p_child = child_device_ptr(p_defs, i);
1163 if (!p_child->common.device_type) {
1164 /* skip the device block if device type is invalid */
1165 continue;
1166 }
1167
1168 if (p_child->common.dvo_port >= DVO_PORT_MIPIA
1169 && p_child->common.dvo_port <= DVO_PORT_MIPID
1170 &&p_child->common.device_type & DEVICE_TYPE_MIPI_OUTPUT) {
1171 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Found MIPI as LFP\n");
1172 dev_priv->vbt.has_mipi = 1;
1173 dev_priv->vbt.dsi.port = p_child->common.dvo_port;
1174 }
1175
1176 child_dev_ptr = dev_priv->vbt.child_dev + count;
1177 count++;
1178
1179 /*
1180 * Copy as much as we know (sizeof) and is available
1181 * (child_dev_size) of the child device. Accessing the data must
1182 * depend on VBT version.
1183 */
1184 memcpy(child_dev_ptr, p_child,
1185 min_t(size_t, p_defs->child_dev_size, sizeof(*p_child)));
1186 }
1187 return;
1188}
1189
1190static void
1191init_vbt_defaults(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv)
1192{
1193 struct drm_device *dev = dev_priv->dev;
1194 enum port port;
1195
1196 dev_priv->vbt.crt_ddc_pin = GMBUS_PIN_VGADDC;
1197
1198 /* Default to having backlight */
1199 dev_priv->vbt.backlight.present = true;
1200
1201 /* LFP panel data */
1202 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_dither = 1;
1203 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_vbt = 0;
1204
1205 /* SDVO panel data */
1206 dev_priv->vbt.sdvo_lvds_vbt_mode = NULL;
1207
1208 /* general features */
1209 dev_priv->vbt.int_tv_support = 1;
1210 dev_priv->vbt.int_crt_support = 1;
1211
1212 /* Default to using SSC */
1213 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_use_ssc = 1;
1214 /*
1215 * Core/SandyBridge/IvyBridge use alternative (120MHz) reference
1216 * clock for LVDS.
1217 */
1218 dev_priv->vbt.lvds_ssc_freq = intel_bios_ssc_frequency(dev,
1219 !HAS_PCH_SPLIT(dev));
1220 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Set default to SSC at %d kHz\n", dev_priv->vbt.lvds_ssc_freq);
1221
1222 for (port = PORT_A; port < I915_MAX_PORTS; port++) {
1223 struct ddi_vbt_port_info *info =
1224 &dev_priv->vbt.ddi_port_info[port];
1225
1226 info->hdmi_level_shift = HDMI_LEVEL_SHIFT_UNKNOWN;
1227
1228 info->supports_dvi = (port != PORT_A && port != PORT_E);
1229 info->supports_hdmi = info->supports_dvi;
1230 info->supports_dp = (port != PORT_E);
1231 }
1232}
1233
1234static int intel_no_opregion_vbt_callback(const struct dmi_system_id *id)
1235{
1236 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Falling back to manually reading VBT from "
1237 "VBIOS ROM for %s\n",
1238 id->ident);
1239 return 1;
1240}
1241
1242static const struct dmi_system_id intel_no_opregion_vbt[] = {
1243 {
1244 .callback = intel_no_opregion_vbt_callback,
1245 .ident = "ThinkCentre A57",
1246 .matches = {
1247 DMI_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "LENOVO"),
1248 DMI_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "97027RG"),
1249 },
1250 },
1251 { .callback = NULL, }
1252};
1253
1254static const struct bdb_header *validate_vbt(const void *base,
1255 size_t size,
1256 const void *_vbt,
1257 const char *source)
1258{
1259 size_t offset = (const char *)_vbt - (const char *)base;
1260 const struct vbt_header *vbt = _vbt;
1261 const struct bdb_header *bdb;
1262
1263 if (offset + sizeof(struct vbt_header) > size) {
1264 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("VBT header incomplete\n");
1265 return NULL;
1266 }
1267
1268 if (memcmp(vbt->signature, "$VBT", 4)) {
1269 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("VBT invalid signature\n");
1270 return NULL;
1271 }
1272
1273 offset += vbt->bdb_offset;
1274 if (offset + sizeof(struct bdb_header) > size) {
1275 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("BDB header incomplete\n");
1276 return NULL;
1277 }
1278
1279 bdb = (const void *)((const char *)base + offset);
1280 if (offset + bdb->bdb_size > size) {
1281 DRM_DEBUG_DRIVER("BDB incomplete\n");
1282 return NULL;
1283 }
1284
1285 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Using VBT from %s: %20s\n",
1286 source, vbt->signature);
1287 return bdb;
1288}
1289
1290#ifdef __NetBSD__
1291# define __iomem __pci_rom_iomem
1292# define ioread32 fake_ioread32
1293static inline uint32_t
1294fake_ioread32(const void __iomem *p)
1295{
1296 uint32_t v;
1297
1298 v = *(const uint32_t __iomem *)p;
1299 __insn_barrier();
1300
1301 return v;
1302}
1303#endif
1304
1305static const struct bdb_header *find_vbt(void __iomem *bios, size_t size)
1306{
1307 const struct bdb_header *bdb = NULL;
1308 size_t i;
1309
1310 /* Scour memory looking for the VBT signature. */
1311 for (i = 0; i + 4 < size; i++) {
1312 if (ioread32((char __iomem *)bios + i) == *((const u32 *) "$VBT")) {
1313 /*
1314 * This is the one place where we explicitly discard the
1315 * address space (__iomem) of the BIOS/VBT. From now on
1316 * everything is based on 'base', and treated as regular
1317 * memory.
1318 */
1319 void *_bios = (void __force *) bios;
1320
1321 bdb = validate_vbt(_bios, size, (char *)_bios + i, "PCI ROM");
1322 break;
1323 }
1324 }
1325
1326 return bdb;
1327}
1328
1329/**
1330 * intel_parse_bios - find VBT and initialize settings from the BIOS
1331 * @dev: DRM device
1332 *
1333 * Loads the Video BIOS and checks that the VBT exists. Sets scratch registers
1334 * to appropriate values.
1335 *
1336 * Returns 0 on success, nonzero on failure.
1337 */
1338int
1339intel_parse_bios(struct drm_device *dev)
1340{
1341 struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv = dev->dev_private;
1342 struct pci_dev *pdev = dev->pdev;
1343 const struct bdb_header *bdb = NULL;
1344 u8 __iomem *bios = NULL;
1345
1346 if (HAS_PCH_NOP(dev))
1347 return -ENODEV;
1348
1349 init_vbt_defaults(dev_priv);
1350
1351 /* XXX Should this validation be moved to intel_opregion.c? */
1352 if (!dmi_check_system(intel_no_opregion_vbt) && dev_priv->opregion.vbt)
1353 bdb = validate_vbt(dev_priv->opregion.header, OPREGION_SIZE,
1354 dev_priv->opregion.vbt, "OpRegion");
1355
1356 if (bdb == NULL) {
1357 size_t size;
1358
1359 bios = pci_map_rom(pdev, &size);
1360 if (!bios)
1361 return -1;
1362
1363 bdb = find_vbt(bios, size);
1364 if (!bdb) {
1365 pci_unmap_rom(pdev, bios);
1366 return -1;
1367 }
1368 }
1369
1370 /* Grab useful general definitions */
1371 parse_general_features(dev_priv, bdb);
1372 parse_general_definitions(dev_priv, bdb);
1373 parse_lfp_panel_data(dev_priv, bdb);
1374 parse_lfp_backlight(dev_priv, bdb);
1375 parse_sdvo_panel_data(dev_priv, bdb);
1376 parse_sdvo_device_mapping(dev_priv, bdb);
1377 parse_device_mapping(dev_priv, bdb);
1378 parse_driver_features(dev_priv, bdb);
1379 parse_edp(dev_priv, bdb);
1380 parse_psr(dev_priv, bdb);
1381 parse_mipi(dev_priv, bdb);
1382 parse_ddi_ports(dev_priv, bdb);
1383
1384 if (bios)
1385 pci_unmap_rom(pdev, bios);
1386
1387 return 0;
1388}
1389
1390#ifdef __NetBSD__
1391# undef __iomem
1392# undef ioread32
1393#endif

1395/**
1396 * intel_bios_is_port_present - is the specified digital port present
1397 * @dev_priv: i915 device instance
1398 * @port: port to check
1399 *
1400 * Return true if the device in %port is present.
1401 */
1402bool intel_bios_is_port_present(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv, enum port port)
1403{
1404 static const struct {
1405 u16 dp, hdmi;
1406 } port_mapping[] = {
1407 [PORT_B] = { DVO_PORT_DPB, DVO_PORT_HDMIB, },
1408 [PORT_C] = { DVO_PORT_DPC, DVO_PORT_HDMIC, },
1409 [PORT_D] = { DVO_PORT_DPD, DVO_PORT_HDMID, },
1410 [PORT_E] = { DVO_PORT_DPE, DVO_PORT_HDMIE, },
1411 };
1412 int i;
1413
1414 /* FIXME maybe deal with port A as well? */
1415 if (WARN_ON(port == PORT_A) || port >= ARRAY_SIZE(port_mapping))
1416 return false;
1417
1418 if (!dev_priv->vbt.child_dev_num)
1419 return false;
1420
1421 for (i = 0; i < dev_priv->vbt.child_dev_num; i++) {
1422 const union child_device_config *p_child =
1423 &dev_priv->vbt.child_dev[i];
1424 if ((p_child->common.dvo_port == port_mapping[port].dp ||
1425 p_child->common.dvo_port == port_mapping[port].hdmi) &&
1426 (p_child->common.device_type & (DEVICE_TYPE_TMDS_DVI_SIGNALING |
1427 DEVICE_TYPE_DISPLAYPORT_OUTPUT)))
1428 return true;
1429 }
1430
1431 return false;
1432}
